# Style and layout

When editing pages or CSS for SWG Audit:

1. **Follow [STYLE.md](/STYLE.md)** (project root) for design tokens, header/footer pattern, simulation banner, and feedback classes.
2. **Header:** One consistent pattern: sticky horizontal bar with `.header-bar` â€” brand (logo + h1), four nav links (Phishing, Malware, Data Theft, Cyberslacking), and right block (About Us, Contribute, GitHub icon). No breadcrumbs. See [STYLE.md](/STYLE.md) for full markup.
3. **Footer:** Same on every page: single paragraph with safety/legal text and links to Terms of Use and Privacy Policy. Sticky at bottom. See [STYLE.md](/STYLE.md) for exact copy and markup.
4. **Feedback:** Use CSS classes `.error` and `.success` for result messages; do not set inline `style.color` in HTML or JavaScript.
5. **CSS:** Add or change styles in [public/css/style.css](public/css/style.css) using existing variables (`--color-*`, `--space-*`, etc.) and place new rules in the correct section (Variables, Reset/base, Layout, Components, Utilities).
